o protection of\n;'i\u2018c and property by \"due process,\u201d and the\nrich' to or-b.p '.vital irods they pleased.\nIt mujorilif -a as to determine who\nwas \u2019e. in he several states ami\nt to!\nn of limited powers constitu\na'U'ad to the federal govern\nmen\nrow beihjr chanced by a\n1\na lace {rtiard and nine \u201cpo\nexalted to life tenure in\nt of th.e land.\nrevolutionary change come\nI\u2019 <tir Mile\u2019s\" i'oveniment have any\nt i u say about it\n11 Coitpre.-s legislate, or did three\n1 m rt s o,' till' states ratify constitutional\namendment-' initiated by \u201cthe people\u2019s\u201d\nivpreserdat;vi'- in (\u2019oupress? Were the 1a.\\\ni'uyic;' i-- of the individual state? con\nsulted i re1 eremlum\nh- 1 led nut of a \"bipartisan\u201d president,\n'os a I'poitit nicnt ot a bipartisan politician\n(;i111-r 1 judicial experience) to\n\u201d''\">ide over our hitriie-d court, broken\nI'icd-es. rank deeeption bv such blun\nders and dishonorable means is the nation\n\u2022\u25a0eh reduced toward a \u201cpeople's povern\npatterned after totalitarianism of\npyramiua! power accepted in Russia, China\nmi their captive populations.\nl!o\\\\ lias all this come about?\n\u201ceooyi, ,sa\\ that \u201cthe politi\ncians\u201d have been playing on the susceptible\nminorities, using \u201cthe loaded dice of the\nemotions.\" That\u2019s the superficial explana\ntion. It is not an excuse.\nThe fault has been ours the great,\nstupid, mentally lazy, self-indulgent, un\norganized majority's.\nThose who did see the drift, knew the\ngame was rigged when a likeable but pliant\nworld war hero posing as a university pres\nident was nominated by a Republican con\nvention so anxious to regain power after 20\nyears of famine that it would have nomi\nnated Beelzebub, had they considered him\nthe only candidate certain of being elected.\nThere wasn't much choice between the\ntwo parties\u2019 champions, with this notable\nexception the leftist Democrats at least\nwere not sailing under false colors. We\nmav deplore their failure to recognize tile\ndrift toward Marxism, but we must grant\nthem this they at least let as know\nwhere they stood.\n\u2022sjt\nSo far as power to protect constitutional\ngovernment is concerned, the conservative\nmajority of America now finds itself the\nvictim of a campaign of calculated treach\nery unprecedented in the history of their\ncountry.\nDo you remember the late Sinclair Lewis'\npolitical novel It Can't Happen Here\nThirty years ago, those of us who read\nit would not have conceded the possiblit.v\nof its happening here let alone the prob\nability\nWe labored under the negligent illusion\nthat the Constitution would ever be a\nmighty fortress against fascism, red or na\ntional socialist. They\u2019d never put anything\nlike that ewer on us. Not on ns. We were too\ncanny. We had been kidded by experts in\nDie fine art of political humbuggery. We\nhad learned by experience to distrust the\nranting demagogue, the bleeding heart, the\nruthless party boss. We\u2019d know how to\nhandle them when the time came.\nWell, Doromus, the newspaper editor in\nl-'ovis' novel was pat riot ica i ly\" convinced\nthat il could not happen here. Ever!\nThe country was foil or Uoremuses. It\nstill is in and outside newspaper offices.\n1 hey and we had forjrotten or ignored\nthe warnings of IUirke. Jefferson, Acton\nthat power corrupts progressively;\nthat \"eternal vigilance\u201d is the price of free\ndom.\nWe smiled tolerantlv at such \u201ccopybook\nmaxims.\u201d\nGod knows how hiyh a price we\u2019ll have to\npay for the folly of over-confidence!\nf abson Disc ussos\nWinter Business Outlook and Russian Satellite\nI':'!': Mas.*. Or! IT. Our\ni* f this year business has\n1 -'ti Uf-rn, which many intfus\nns uiceuntered and with\ninch .-ein still ha vine to con*\nad physical volume of\ns'lt'd:. is cot: ontly only a trifle\n\u2022low ram; of recent\n\u2018;ton*as a:.! :s uist a lew percentage\npoint.- \u2018r \u20191 i.in the first-quarter\nfak to; tin yo;u' to date. During\nt\u201ce -atnrnior. many businesses have\nI\u25a0'\u2022(\u25a0\u00bb drawn downward because of\n\u2022\u2022\u2022asi.u.d influences such, a.* hot\nv-ideii and vacation absences\nI expect business during\nci in'... months to be moderately\nuuw: h helped i v the Russian\nsat el i..t\nHowet e: the improvement de\nlists :]-f upon basic consumer atti\nlie- 'i-h\u2019ch can chance from day\nday Recent surveys .m consumer\nb1\u2019 lid attitudes indicate that\n\u2018\u25a0'ire: -J; tipiaurniiu more price\nticnsei 11 cui :11\u25a0 selectivi Never\ni ole.' 1 clfactuivv art hopeful\nthat lieu: uc- mid output sch.'d\nU-'s J\u201e! months will tally\nclosely wuh tin purcini; uw plate\n\u25a0if Cie'Di ers. which arc still con\nundue upward\nThe \\uto Outlook\nThe au'ompbde industry is ;i\nwether of foilhceminr trends\nDealt .\u2018foes-- cutn-mly near\ni;\u2022 ;<t.1\u00bb11 t! s-n; ,7 ears\nwith ea.'v spt inkling of th5t>\nmodels Th!> far. here has been\nlittle iproe) r a dine the\n'r .uii'mehih. invent ones, and\ne: .lie! ,,l HHH\u2019lui October\nies w.: ist app:. teh those of\nTi l don ret 1 ummiKlU\ns.UKJtu: aii'tomoblir makers is holp\nto bet\" the steal industry which\nceiitinues t i hop* !'ii a strcngthen\nMit: t.\u00bbt orders Though such orders\nr lie.- eointup :r. .ttadnallv\nm mii.v wrk may see a greater\nrush as the remainder of the plants\nchany' over to the production of\nlu.'iJ! cars Appliance makers are\nalso proceeding cautiously with res\npect to orders since sales have been\ndisappointing so far this year. How\nevi r. as inventories in these lines\nKeister declines, factory output\nshotiid gradually trend up.\nConstruction Industry\nAnother major steel user, the\nconstruction industry, appears to\nhave been taking a breather, al\nthough the latest month's figures\nshow a more-than-seasonal rise after\nthe disappointing earlier weeks.\nWork stoppages in the cement in\ndustry caused shortages of concrete\nproducts in some sectors There are,\nhowever, more basic reasons for\nth slower pace in building, such as\nscarcity of money and the partial\nfulfillment of demand for housing.\nSustaining strength, however, should\nhe evident in public works,mltilities.\nand read building.\ntM'Noiin in.' conundrum ot what\nthe consumer is going to do with\nlit'- income sonit* consumer-expendi\nture plans are already being af\nfected lay lowei expenditures by the\nI). \u2018east Department Military cut\nbacks are beginning to affect whole\ncommunities which are largely de\nr rdent upon government contracts,\nsue!) as aircraft workers and others i\nemployed in these towns dependent j\nspoil military payrolls The Russian\nsatellite may, however, change all.\nthis\nWhat About Kniployment?\nThose who are laid off .will bo\nless eager to spend and will hesitate\nto co further into debt: wtjile those\nwho remain on the payroll may be\nceme more cautious about spend\nOn the other hand, due to the\ni iig period of boom, the average\nconsumer has become accustomed\nto an increasingly higher standard\nof living. And it is far harder to\nadjust one's tastes downward than\nto raise them upward.\nHigher wages are partly responsi\nble for the continued rise in personal\nincomes. However, these increases\nin pay rates are a cause for con\ncern to producers, since they add to\nthe cost of doing business. Coupled\nwith lower sales in certain lines,\nthey further squeeze profits.\nConclusions\nAll in all. coming months should\nshow a modest improvement over\nthe lows of the summer months.\nBut the degree of improvement is\ndependent on a revival of consumer\nexpenditures, which in turn are af\nfected by capital outlays and by\nchanges in government spending,\nwhich could Ire increased as a re\nsull of the Russian satellite sur\nprise. It may well be that all three\nfactors have been merely hesitating\nin order to consolidate the gains of\nthe past long boom. Much will de\npend upon advertising, appropria\ntions and tire efficiency of selling.\nHog Grading Program\n*u\u2018t Oct. 2.*} at 2 p. m.\nR S. Ellis. Buckingham County\nagent. said today, a marketing\ndemonstration on hogs would be\nheld at the farm of V. C. Proffitt,\nWednesday. Oct. 23 at 2 p. m.\nProffitt's farm is located on Rt.\n15 about seven miles south of\nSprouses Corner or about a mile\nnorth of Curdsvilic.\nRoy Ciodsey. swine specialist\nfrom VPI will explain the type of\nhog that is selling for a premium\non today's market and why it\nbrings top prices. He will also\ndemonstrate a hog grading pro\ngram.\nLetters To Editor\nBirds Add Color\nTo Beautiful Nature\nEditor of Herald:\nWhile Mother Nature is attired\nin her most beautiful garb, if 1\n\u2018eems an opportune time to re\ncount some of the activities of my 5\ndear'bird friends.\nThey render such lovely music\nthese days, although some of the\nmigrants have taken their depar\nture and will enjoy a warmer cli\nmate. It seems quite strange that\nthe female mocking birds should\nleave thei\u2019- mates and go south\ntor the winter.\nI am pleased that the cardinals\nspend the entire year with us, and\nthe lady bird joins in the singing,\nas she is the only female that is\ntalented.\nDickie bird comes very early in\ntile morning for his raisins. He is\nquite indignant if he is not served\nimmediately. I have spoiled him.\nno doubt.\nThis is the most beautiful\nmonth of the year, or it is my\nfavorite. The world is a lovely\npicture now. and artists paint\nwonderfully, but not to compare\nwith tlie one made by God.\nAll of my birds join me in\nwishing you the best of health\nand happiness. Don't fail to feed\nthe birds. Be sure to drive care\nfully.\nBirdie May Baueh\nPowhatan\nCommends Town\nFor Effieencv\n\nEditor of Herald:\nI am writing in regard to an\naccident which happened at the\nintersection of Fourth and Vir\nginia Streets this afternoon, at\nwhich time a truck loaded with\nhundreds of soft drink bottles\noverturned and. covered a large\narea of the road with broken\nglass.\nThe driver was taken to the\nhospital and when I returned to\nthe scene of the accident I found\nthat the Town crew under the\nable supervision of H. W. Derey.\nhad removed all of ihe glass from\nthe street so efficiently that you\ncould not tell an accident had\neven occurred.\nI feel that they should be com\nmended for their most efficient\nservice to this community, partic\nularly when a situation such as\nthis exists.\nVery truly yours\nRobert B. Burger\nOctober 18. 1957\nCOLORED NEWS\n4-H, NFA Hoj?\nShow, Sale To Be\nAt Lynchburg Oct. 21\nCumberland County 4-H and NFA\nboys will participate in the Junior\nMarket Show and Sale at the Lynch\nburg City Stadium on Thursriin\nOct. 24. beginning at 10 a m This\n.show will feature animals grown by\nyouths in thc-ir 1 H and NFA proj\nects.\nThe show and sale is open to 4-H\nor NFA members from the counties\nof Albemarle, Amelia. Appomattox,\nBuckingham, Campbell. Char\nlotte. Cumberland. Halifax. Bed\nford. Lunenburg. Nottoway. Powha\ntan, Prince Edward, Amherst and\nFranklin. The object is to derpon\n!strate good breeding, selection, sani\ntation. use of high protein' and\nj mineral supplements, use of self\n'feeders and also to show the proper\nj type of hogs to produce for market.\nAll animals will be graded into\nUS No. 1. US No. 2. US No.3 or\ni US Mediums. Representatives of the\nj Division of Markets will do the\ngrading. Judging of the animals will\nbe done by J. E. Settle, of the\nAnimal Husbandry Department. Vir\njginia State College.\nJohn Temple Graves\nCreations Of God\nInspire Columnist\n\"Tacoma\u2014the Mountain\nthat was God\nUnited Airline over the Rockies\u2014 j\nEvery 90 minutes, as of -now. the j\nRussian satellite rides above what j\nSeattler.s call Mt, .Rainier but the!\nIndians called \"Tacoma,\" meaning;\n\"the mountain that was God.\" They\ncalled it that for the mighty crest\nof it above mists that.detach it from\nthe earth.\nBut seen from air as this plane!\npassed it an hour ago. it was no\nmore than an ant hill, or an Indian\nmound\nAnd from the Russian moon, of\ncourse, it is't even a pinpoint\nAre we poor Indians\u2014aren't we\nall-belittled and lost bv what our\nscientists learn? I think we may\nhave been for a time but now we\nbegin to be saturated with 'hese\nimmensities with si/e. speed,\nspace, high explosion and that\nenormous generality called \"so\nciety,\" I think we begin to come\nhome to measurements other than\nthe physical 'or the social We see\nor remember\u2014that the real meas\nurements are in the hearts and\nsouls of us, the immortal longings,\nthe intimations of immortality, the\nhigh and i\u00a3her cult of the indi\nvidual.\nThe \"mountain that was God\" is\nstill a mountain that was God, You\nneed only to know where- or from\nwhere\u2014to look\nNow that Russia's home run has\nchallenged America to wake .up and\nwin the game, the old song will\nturn plural. It wilL.be \"the moons\nhave their eyes on you.\nWhose mind is one quirk in? It\nmay be my own but this triple\nschool \"compromise\" plan David\nLawrence reports impresses me now\nas heretofore as a mere play on\nwords. One of the three schools\nwould be a white one from which\nNegroes would he excluded by law.\nThat's exactly what the Supreme\nCourt damned\n\"When it\u2019s springtime in the\nRockies\" how do .the Rockii s, in\ntheir nakedness, know 1\nSpeaking of the Washington state\njudges, who agreed\u2019 with me so in\nTacoma last night and the hope of\na constitutional grand alliance\nswelled and distinguished by the\njudicial i. of the stales, th. scath\ning criticism qf the United States\nSupreme Court by Arizona's Su\npreme Court Justice M. T. Phelps\nis getting an immense circulation\nif enclosut in my mail mean any\nthing He sees in the present court\na deliberate design to \u201cusurp the\npolio making powers of the\nnation,\" a n'-.c of the Fourteenth\nAmendin' it to destroy the rights\nnot only of states hut of practically\nevery business m the nation, and a\ngreatei danger to our democratic\nform of gov. i mem and the Ameri\ncan way of iife toon all forces\nI aligned against u outside our bound\naries t5\nI wonder what psychiatrists woulc\nPaid Political Advertisement\nRepublican Campaign Committee\nGRAY'S\nTRULY A\nDRUG STORE\nNOT ON YOUR LIFE!\nYour prescription may look\nmysterious with its Symbols,\nabbreviations, Latin terms\nbut there Is nothing secretive\nabout it.\nThink a minute don't mesi\nclans, engineers, lawyers, oc\ncountonts in fact, doesn't\nanyone in a skilled profession,\nincluding yourself\u2014use technical\nterminology to communicate pre\ncise information?\nActually, the way your pre\nscription reads facilitates and\nmakes certain that you get ex\nactly what the doctor orders.\nYOUR PHARMACIST\nTHE\nPHARMACISTS\nART\nAT IT\u2019S\nBEST\nGray's Drugstore\nPHONE 56 FARMVILLE, VA. PHONE 57\nay of an ego-mania which lets nine\nnen who have been elected to noth\nng and who have no mandate from\nCongress take it upon themselves to\n:io this country overr\nMeals brought aboard United Air\nLines planes at Denver are Rocky\nMountain\u2014high in gastronomic dis\nmction. The meun card tells you\n[hey have been prepared by Conrad\nKung, chef, \"member Societe Culi\nnaire Philanthropique. Vice Presi\ndent, Colorado Chefs de Cuisine As\nsociation,\" That's eating high.\nDouble Check\nHaving lost face in Mid East\nwe now line up with The British\nwho have lost everything in order\nto get a football against an aggra\nvated Communistic satilite group\nthat have set plans to rule the\nWorld. While our scientists take\nphotos of the Sun we defer\nlaunching a new moon for fear\nof failure or collusion with one\ntiiat sails the mighty stratosphere\non a jeep, jeep, jeep, and peep,\npeep. peep, and we sleep, sleep,\nevidently awaiting annihilation.\nThe administration and the\nPentagon are a worried lot. The\nonly thins cheap in America is a\nRepublican. There may be a cure\nfor what ails us, but it ain't poll\ntics. What we need is some real\ndeep thinking watch dogs of our j\nentire future, real statesmen, who j\nthink and do for the best interest\nof this great nation of. was, ours j\nit ain't anymore. We are j\nfloating off on a have religious\nidealistic idea of degradeing su- i\npremacy that it takes a brain 1\nreader to understand and j\nthen you can't understand. Under\nfile present set up we are bound j\nl to go down. We are LOST in a\nsea of professional imagination1\nwhile we go to and fro criticizing\nleach other. Before our judiciary\nwe rise to, \"May it please the\ncourt\", never thinking that \"may\n\u2022it please God\". Guess I'm just an\nj old fogey, especially in this age\ni where you split everything fiom\nthe atom to the brain, and just\ni take another aspirin\nThanks for reading.\nYours,\nJ. Marvin Brown\nTomato powder \"Tor use in sauces.\n1 soups, juice and dry mixes, may!\njsoon be available commencally. The\npowder mixes readily with water to\nmake a highly acceptable juice. It\ncan be stored indefinitely without:\n1 refrigeration.\nA foetid Tax Assessment Ratio Set At\n30 Per Pent by County Supervisors\nAn inc r e i e d assessment for\nAmelia count,S '.pf approximately the\ndifference bet'/pen- the current mar\nket values antjjthose of seven years\nago was antic sated last week.\nIn a closed ?Venhg of the Amelia\nboard of supervisors and the county\nboard of reaft*fstite assessors, the\ncounty' ratio-'- ior> tax asessment\npurposes wai/'set at 80 per cent.\nA 40 per Centura! 10 was used from\n1950 to 1956.\nAmelia, whipli has been in the\nprocess of re assessment most of th\u00b0\nyear, will have a new rate based\nupon conservative 1957 mark e t\nvalues, effective next July 1\nBy July 1, ffif county must also\nreaffirm the foment rate of 52.90\nper $100 asse. ;ed valuation, or es\ntablish a ne\\t rme for the 1958\n1959 fiscal ydj i.\nMore than 3 per cent of the\ncounty has |jt*n' reappraised ant)\nreviewed byjC